commit_message:
Update master branch with v0.1 release
$ git checkout master
$ git merge --no-ff develop

Ref: https://nvie.com/posts/a-successful-git-branching-model/

Merge branch 'develop'

Minor updates to documentation
- Added badges for bioconda and licence
- Cleaned up installation instructions
Bump version number for bioconda submission

Add a bunch of missing imports
- Fixes "NameError: name 'idr' is not defined"
- Now runs successfully on CD14 DNase (Epigenomics Roadmap)

Calling IDR: add notes & move code to separate file

Aspirational docstring examples:
- https://sphinxcontrib-napoleon.readthedocs.io/en/latest/example_google.html
- https://sphinxcontrib-napoleon.readthedocs.io/en/latest/example_numpy.html

Show yapc version on startup & related tweaks

- setup.py explicitly import yapc.__version__ as suggested in:
    https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0396/#classic-distutils

- __init__.py change from double to single quotes:
    https://stackoverflow.com/questions/56011/single-quotes-vs-double-quotes-in-python

- Longer commit messages inspired by:
    https://fatbusinessman.com/2019/my-favourite-git-commit
    https://blog.mocoso.co.uk/talks/2015/01/12/telling-stories-through-your-commits/

Refactor code for pypi/bioconda

Can now run `pip install -e .` to do the following:
- make `bin/yapc` available as a script in the current python environment
- pip correctly checks for dependancies defined in setup.py
- idr does not seem to be on pypi, only on bioconda
Notes on citing and using on isolated replicates
Rudimentary support for pseudoreplicates by specifying --pseudoreplicates
Allow for empty chromosomes in (some) input tracks (e.g. short sequences in Ensembl CB4)
Call IDR directly instead of wrapping via os.system()
Moved yapc to a standalone repository + added documentation
